HEADWORD: Nolition
<hw>No*li"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nolle</ets> not to will, to be unwilling; <ets>ne + velle</ets> to
will, to be willing.]</ety> <def>Adverse action of will; unwillingness;
-- opposed to <ant>volition</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>nolition</qex> and a direct enmity against the lust.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noll</ent>⟦br⟧
